WEBVTT

00:19.587 --> 00:23.725
<i>Currently
it's 72 right now, with
those winds on the calm side.</i>

00:23.758 --> 00:27.161
<i>It's just a glorious
Tuesday morning here
in Pittsburgh.</i>

00:27.194 --> 00:28.696
<i>We can see around us...</i>

00:28.730 --> 00:30.865
<i>Dear Zoe.</i>

00:30.899 --> 00:33.367
<i>Reports of a tie-up
on I-79 north of the city...</i>

00:33.401 --> 00:36.270
<i>I have memories
of you from before
you were even born.</i>

00:36.303 --> 00:38.338
<i>I just remember us
sitting around the kitchen,</i>

00:38.372 --> 00:40.274
<i>arguing about
what your name should be...</i>

00:42.142 --> 00:43.778
<i>...and how that somehow
made you a real person</i>

00:43.812 --> 00:45.613
<i>before I even saw you face.</i>

00:48.148 --> 00:52.186
<i>Mom told us Zoe means life,
that this name would
protect you...</i>

00:52.219 --> 00:54.021
Zoe!

00:54.054 --> 00:56.858
<i>but nothing could have
protected you that day,</i>

00:56.891 --> 00:59.794
<i>except me, and I didn't.</i>

01:01.930 --> 01:05.265
<i>-I was just an ordinary girl
with ordinary problems.
-Mom!</i>

01:05.299 --> 01:08.202
<i>Divorced parents,
annoying stepdad,</i>

01:08.235 --> 01:09.737
<i>lousy grades.</i>

01:09.771 --> 01:12.105
<i>Kind of lousy friends.</i>

01:12.139 --> 01:15.577
<i>But you,
you were extraordinary,</i>

01:15.610 --> 01:17.946
<i>and I loved being
your big sister.</i>

01:17.978 --> 01:20.981
<i>I'd get pissed if someone
said you were only
my half-sister,</i>

01:21.014 --> 01:23.418
<i>because you were never
half of anything.</i>

01:23.451 --> 01:25.854
<i>...as the towers
of the World Trade Center...</i>

01:25.887 --> 01:28.222
<i>But then you
left us</i>

01:28.255 --> 01:30.758
<i>on the worst day
imaginable.</i>

01:30.792 --> 01:33.260
<i>It's right on top of us right now.
We gotta get out of the way!</i>

01:33.293 --> 01:35.763
<i>On the news,
they've been saying all year</i>

01:35.797 --> 01:37.632
<i>that history
will forever be divided</i>

01:37.665 --> 01:42.102
<i>between what happened
before 9/11 and after.</i>

01:42.135 --> 01:44.271
<i>But that erases your death,</i>

01:44.304 --> 01:48.242
<i>because you died on that day
but not because of that day.</i>

01:48.275 --> 01:51.044
<i>You died because of me.</i>

01:53.681 --> 01:57.384
Along the way, you might
experience anxiety,

01:57.418 --> 02:00.688
depression,
anger, even guilt.

02:00.722 --> 02:04.124
Whenever you feel the urge,
write down in these notebooks

02:04.157 --> 02:05.927
anything you want
to say or to remember.

02:05.960 --> 02:08.362
Why would we want
to remember any of this?

02:12.901 --> 02:15.703
- Tessie!
- Tess, get back here!

02:17.906 --> 02:21.108
Hey, sweetie, it's okay.

02:21.141 --> 02:22.610
Come here.

02:26.213 --> 02:28.550
That was rude.

02:28.583 --> 02:31.719
I'm done talking, and I won't
write in any stupid notebook.

02:31.753 --> 02:35.122
So, you guys,
you can enjoy your trip
down "recovery road,"

02:35.155 --> 02:36.624
but I'm not going.

02:36.658 --> 02:38.459
You gonna tell her that?

02:42.396 --> 02:45.833
We need to do it
to get better.

02:45.867 --> 02:47.301
Come on, sweetie.

03:39.454 --> 03:43.190
<i>Guilt and grief
are a powerful combination.</i>

03:43.223 --> 03:45.927
<i>They make you question things
you used to do before.</i>

03:45.960 --> 03:48.730
Less time on makeup, more time on breakfast.
Come on!

03:48.763 --> 03:52.399
<i>Like, how I'd get
into disturbingly
in-depth discussions with Em</i>

03:52.433 --> 03:54.535
<i>about how you'd always
stink up the bathroom.</i>

03:54.569 --> 03:56.269
Ohhh!

03:56.303 --> 03:58.606
<i>And how I'd pick
my daily fight with David</i>

03:58.640 --> 04:01.876
<i>about wanting
to go to art school
instead of college.</i>

04:01.909 --> 04:07.048
<i>And my weekly fight with Mom
about not wanting to spend
time over at my dad's.</i>

04:07.081 --> 04:11.753
<i>Or how I used to gossip
about boys with my friends
on the bus</i>

04:11.786 --> 04:18.158
<i>and suffer through long,
boring days at school...</i>

04:18.191 --> 04:21.095
<i>when I'd much rather
have just stayed home
and played with you all day.</i>

04:21.129 --> 04:22.597
Oh, come here!

04:22.630 --> 04:24.398
Ohh! Mmm!

04:24.432 --> 04:26.100
<i>Then we could have all gone
to the market...</i>

04:26.134 --> 04:28.069
Oh, you're gonna
have a funnel cake.

04:28.102 --> 04:30.337
<i>...where I could have
flirted with cute Justin.</i>

04:30.370 --> 04:32.607
<i>And you could have flirted
with cute Justin.</i>

04:32.640 --> 04:35.777
And now to bag
this sack of potatoes!

04:35.810 --> 04:38.245
Motatoes!

04:38.278 --> 04:40.915
<i>Maybe if I did
something different,</i>

04:40.948 --> 04:42.784
<i>things would be different.</i>

04:42.817 --> 04:44.852
<i>Or maybe not.</i>

04:44.886 --> 04:46.888
<i>I honestly
just don't know anymore.</i>

04:48.823 --> 04:52.325
<i>Because at the end
of every goddamn day,</i>

04:52.359 --> 04:54.128
<i>reality set in...</i>

04:56.564 --> 04:59.701
<i>...and I was just left
with before...</i>

